                <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/2780: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Acting American Representative to the French Committee of National
                        Liberation at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-08T00:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 8, 1944—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>415. Reference your 358, February 3, 6 p.m. The Department’s telegram to Rabat of
                    January 31 was intended solely to serve as a guide in any conversations which
                    our officers might have on the subject of the nationalist movement in Morocco.
                    If you are asked for an expression of this Government’s views in the matter, you
                    may reply along the lines described, but no need is perceived for you to take
                    the initiative in presenting our position to Massigli.</p>
                <p>Repeat to Rabat.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
